@NODE "Installation" "Installation"
@WORDWRAP
WinBack III need no special assigns, just copy it anywhere.

But, you need CrossDOS and MUI installed...
@ENDNODE
@NODE "Usage" "Usage"
@WORDWRAP
Read @{"   important   " LINK "Important"} now!

@{U}Start-up:@{UU}
@{B}From Workbench:@{UB}
Double-click the icon...

@{B}From CLI:@{UB}
WinBackIII [SOURCE] [DESTINATION]

SOURCE - your backup file
  example: WinBackIII PC0:MYBACK.QIC
DESTINATION - destination directory
  example: WinBackIII PC0:MYBACK.QIC Ram:

@{U}The GUI:@{UU}
@{B}Info-box:@{UB}
Errors and warnings are shown here.

@{B}Source:@{UB}
Here you enter your backup-filename, or use the popup-button and select the file from the ASL-requester.
Important: see @{"   bugs   " LINK "Bugs"}

@{B}Destination:@{UB}
Here you enter the destination directory where you want your files restored, or use the popup-button and select the file from the ASL-requester.

@{B}Filelist:@{UB}
Here you can select which file(s) you want to restore, either by selecting them with the mouse/keyboard or by using the ALL/NONE/TOGGLE buttons below the filelist.
Doubleclicking a name in the list displays some information in the info-window: file name, file size and the backupdisk-number the file starts on.

@{B}Restore-button:@{UB}
Press it to restore the files you selected.

@{B}Abort-button:@{UB}
Press it to stop the restoring.

@{B}Tip: Insert the last disk of the backup-set first, this way you'll get a complete file-list.@{UB}
  WinBack III will display a warning if the disk does not contain a list of all the files in the backup.
@ENDNODE
